ol.li:
If you add a catch(...) block be sure to add the following block

      catch(const OutOfMemoryException&)
	{
		throw;
	}
       so the OutOfMemory condition does not get absorbed.

Update the website by taking a binary package and extracting the doc/html directories. The web pages are stored in /www/xml.apache.org/xerces-c. You will also need to update the documentation pdf in the pdf directory (which has both a pdf and pdf.tar.gz). Recommend copying the new documentation over the existing files. Be sure to change the permissions on the files and directories:
find . -type f -exec chmod 664 {} ;
find . -type d -exec chmod 775 {} ;
If the binaries are for different platforms you may also need to update the download.html file to point to the new binaries.
Verify that the website is updated (may take a while to be refreshed on the real webserver).
